                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Robert Winfield. This is my tea-pot - I have had no quarrel with the prisoner.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that a man named Pascall, who he saw at a public-house, had sent him to fetch the tea-pot to dispose of for him. He received a good character.</p>
               <p>ELIZABETH WINFIELD. I know nothing of a person named Pascall - I do not know whether he was in the house; I believe the prisoner did say a man named Pascall had sent him for it.</p>
